alisa [name[=value]]

list create aliases

Fix Typos:
$ alias grpe='grep'

Make linux behave like another OS.

$alias cls='clear'

To remove an alias:

unalias name 

Remove all aliases

unalias -a

Add aliases to your presonal initialization files.
.bash_profile

ls -l as an alias

alias ll='ls -l'

clear
alias cls='clear'

to list alias

alias

to make them persist:

add them to the .bash_profile

alias mycls='clear'

logout and the logback in to check

